  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "29c4750c-f3ba-8082-be75-c1f0f03b60f4",
      "heading": "Summary Table REC",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "Active Learning",
          "Content-Based Filtering",
          "Personalized Solutions to Learning Challenges",
          "55 students (Summer 2021)Historic reflections: 186 students (2020–2021)",
          "1 course, 14 weeks of reflections",
          "– Student reflection texts (2 prompts per week)\n\n– Historical dataset of prior students’ “challenges” and “solutions”",
          "Sentence embeddings initialized with pre-trained stsb-roberta-large transformer (no fine-tuning)",
          "Static: no retraining during deployment\n\nRecommendations recomputed for new students using existing reflection corpus",
          "– Removed incomplete or short reflections\n\n– Token cleaning and normalization– Sentence-to-vector encoding (RoBERTa embeddings)\n\n– Cosine similarity top-k (k=5) retrieval",
          "Top-5 Solutions to Reported Challenges",
          "{Membership: 0.83 → 0.86, Acceptance: 0.62→0.70, Trust: 0.75→0.81, Fade: -0.34→-0.48}",
          "– Novel reflection-driven educational recommender leveraging NLP (semantic similarity) rather than grades or logs.\n\n– Encourages peer empathy and sense of belonging by connecting similar challenges.\n\n– No labeled data needed (unsupervised, lightweight).\n\n– Demonstrates positive affective outcomes and high perceived usefulness.",
          "– Small pilot sample (N = 16 post-survey).\n\n– Dependence on reflection quality; vague or humorous answers degrade results.\n\n– Lack of adaptive feedback (static corpus).\n\n– Negative correlation between similarity & usefulness suggests semantic proximity ≠ pedagogical value.\n\n– Limited generalization (single course, single institution)."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
